<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="529" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1269,1618]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1305,1330]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body length 5.0–6.0 mm; male holoptic; general colour brown with grey pollinosity; scutum with an “ 
<taxonomicName box="[198,319,1341,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Anthomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[198,319,1341,1365]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Anthomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-pattern”, the two presutural dark brown spots completely or almost completely fused; postsutural band broad; scutellum dark brown, grey pollinose only at apex; notopleuron grey pollinose; frons brown; antenna, arista and palpus brown; haltere yellow; legs brown; frontal triangle short; arista plumose; postsutural dorsocentrals 4, the first 2 short; lower katepisternal weak, inserted closer to the long posterior one; fore tibia without a submedian seta; mid femur with 2 preapical setae, one posterior and one posterodorsal; mid tibia with 2 posterior setae; sternite 1 bare; sternite 5 as in 
<figureCitation box="[671,753,1521,1546]" captionStart="FIGURES 89 – 103" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[190,1408,221,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 89 – 103. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view (not figured for L. quadristriata); epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 89 – 91. Limnophora quadristriata Emden. 92 – 95. Limnophora sinuosa sp. nov. 96 – 99. Limnophora somereni Emden. 100 – 103. Limnophora spinata Stein." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242403/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1269,1618]" box="[199,1190,1557,1582]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
Terminalia. Cercal plate and surstylus as in 
<figureCitation box="[688,817,1557,1582]" captionStart="FIGURES 89 – 103" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[190,1408,221,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 89 – 103. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view (not figured for L. quadristriata); epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 89 – 91. Limnophora quadristriata Emden. 92 – 95. Limnophora sinuosa sp. nov. 96 – 99. Limnophora somereni Emden. 100 – 103. Limnophora spinata Stein." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242403/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Figs 97–98</figureCitation>
. Aedeagal complex as in 
<figureCitation box="[1103,1185,1557,1582]" captionStart="FIGURES 89 – 103" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[190,1408,221,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 89 – 103. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view (not figured for L. quadristriata); epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 89 – 91. Limnophora quadristriata Emden. 92 – 95. Limnophora sinuosa sp. nov. 96 – 99. Limnophora somereni Emden. 100 – 103. Limnophora spinata Stein." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242403/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Fig. 99</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
